"adj. 喜悦的，欢呼的 【英】 adj. 喜悦的，欢呼的(elat ed; rejoicing) 【考】 反义词：dolorous(忧 伤的) 【记】 jubil(大叫)+ ant→高兴得大叫 【同】 派生词: jubilation (n. 喜悦，欢呼) 【例】 Bill was jubilant when he finally beat his older brother at chess. adj. 喜悦的; 喜气洋洋的 【记】ju猪, bil = bill, ant: 猪, 钞票和蚂蚁, 你选那个? 肯定是钞票, 所以特别高兴. 读: 卓别林t－给人带来欢乐 【反】dolorous(adj 忧伤悲痛的) 【记】音: 卓别林，卓别林给人们带来喜悦与欢呼；job + ill 工作时病了→可以不上班休息白拿钱了→欢呼 jubilant (adj.)  1660s, from Latin jubilantem (nominative jubilans), present participle of jubilare ""to call to someone,"" in Christian writers, ""to shout for joy,"" related to jubilum ""wild shout."" First attested in Milton. Related: Jubilantly."
